  "text": "In addition to the aromatic cage, the β2−β3 loop directly participates in histone interaction as it forms one of the walls of the binding pocket [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . The β2 −β3 loop is the region that differs mostly among PWWP domains. These structural differences suggest that the β2 −β3 loop may be implicated in determining ligand binding specificity. It is worth noting that the methyl-lysine binding pocket is located in a different position than the DNA binding site. Therefore, PWWP domains employ distinct but contiguous interfaces for binding histones and DNA [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] ).",
